    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Algolia doesn't (yet) support the concept of \"hierarchical facets\". A hierarchical facet is a concept that exists at the Helper level. It adds the facet to the `facets` search parameter.\r\n\r\nYou should therefore be able to see your hierarchical facet attribute in `helper.state.facets`.",
    "created_at": "2020-04-08T14:25:25Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4377#issuecomment-610990671",
