    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @francoischalifour \r\nThank you for this answer.\r\nI indeed notice it in `helper.state.facets`. But the issue is that *in the results*, at render time, `results.facets` *disappears* when you mount the `breadcrumb` widget.\r\nI need to avoid cross-widget dependency.\r\n\r\nExample :\r\n```\r\nrender: function (renderOptions) {\r\nconsole.log( renderOptions.results)\r\n```\r\nThe above will show  :\r\n* `facets` populated when no `breadcrumb` widget is used, and  `hierarchicalFacets` empty.\r\n* `hierarchicalFacets` populated and  `facets` empty otherwise\r\n",
